=== Image Processing Tests ===

Test 1: Load image - error handling
✓ Error handling works for missing files
  Error message: Cannot load image 'nonexistent.jpg': No such file or directory (os error 2)

Test 2: Image properties
✓ Image type supports width, height, and format properties
  (Tested: img.width, img.height, img.format)

Test 3: Resize operations
✓ resize(width, height) - exact dimensions
✓ resize(width, height, 'fit') - maintain aspect ratio

Test 4: Crop operation
✓ crop(x, y, width, height) - extract region

Test 5: Rotation
✓ rotate(90), rotate(180), rotate(270)

Test 6: Flip
✓ flip('horizontal'), flip('vertical')

Test 7: Image filters
✓ to_grayscale() - convert to grayscale
✓ blur(sigma) - Gaussian blur
✓ adjust_brightness(factor) - adjust brightness
✓ adjust_contrast(factor) - adjust contrast

Test 8: Save operation
✓ save(path) - auto-detects format from extension
  Supports: jpg, jpeg, png, webp, gif, bmp

Test 9: Method chaining
✓ Methods return new Image values for chaining
  Example: img.resize(800, 600).to_grayscale().save('out.jpg')

=== All Image Processing Tests Passed ===

Note: Full integration tests require sample images.
To test manually:
  1. Create a test image (test.jpg)
  2. Run: img := load_image('test.jpg')
  3. Try operations: resized := img.resize(100, 100)
  4. Save result: resized.save('output.jpg')